# Arabic VAT Invoice Generator

This project is a simple web page for generating Arabic VAT invoices. Users can input seller and buyer information, item descriptions, prices, and VAT rates to create a VAT invoice.

## Features

- Input fields for seller name, buyer name, item description, item price, and VAT rate.
- Calculates and displays the VAT amount and total price.
- Supports right-to-left text alignment for Arabic content.

## Usage

1. Open the web page.
2. Fill in the seller name, buyer name, item description, item price, and VAT rate.
3. Click the "إنشاء الفاتورة" (Create Invoice) button to generate the invoice.
4. The generated invoice will be displayed below the form.

## Files

- `index.html`: The main HTML file containing the structure of the web page.
- `styles.css`: The CSS file for styling the web page.
- `script.js`: The JavaScript file containing the logic to generate the invoice.

## How to Deploy

1. Clone the repository or download the files.
2. Open the `index.html` file in a web browser to view the page locally.
3. To make it live, follow the instructions in the "GitHub Pages" section below.

## GitHub Pages

This project can be hosted on GitHub Pages. Follow these steps to deploy:

1. Create a new GitHub repository.
2. Upload the `index.html`, `styles.css`, `script.js`, and `README.md` files to the repository.
3. Go to the "Settings" tab of your repository.
4. Scroll down to the "GitHub Pages" section.
5. Under "Source", select the branch (usually `main`) and the folder (usually `/root` or `/docs`) where your `index.html` file is located.
6. Click "Save".
7. Your site will be available at `https://yourusername.github.io/your-repo-name/`.

